# Final Validation

Before finalizing, verify:

* Every milestone represents implemented capability.
* Every milestone leaves the software objectively more capable.
* The sequence follows implementation dependency.
* No milestone exists solely to organize work.
* No milestone exists primarily to produce human-readable artifacts.
* Architecture emerges in service of implementation.
* Tests validate implemented behavior rather than substitute for implementation.
* The roadmap preserves the intent established by the conversation.
* The roadmap stands on its own without requiring the design discussion.

